# RULE: No hardcoded identity or auth protocol (LOCKED)

**ID:** `rule_no_hardcoded_identity_auth_protocol` | **Priority:** ALWAYS | **D1:** `agentsam_rules_document`

This agreement is **non-negotiable**. Violations are treated as **security defects** (wrong tenant isolation, wrong allowlist rows, consent bound to the wrong user).

## Forbidden in live code paths

Never embed these as **literals** in `src/`, `dashboard/`, or MCP server `src/` (request handlers, guards, consent, token issue, tool dispatch):

| Pattern | Examples (forbidden) |
|---------|----------------------|
| User ids | `au_871d920d1233cbd1`, any `au_[hex]` |
| Workspace ids | `ws_inneranimalmedia`, any `ws_[slug]` used as runtime default |
| Tenant ids | `tenant_sam_primeaux`, any `tenant_*` used as runtime default |
| Operator email | `sam@inneranimalmedia.com`, `info@inneranimals.com` in logic branches |
| Migration seeds | `INSERT … allowlist` / `user_policy` with specific `au_*` + `ws_*` for one human |

```js
// ❌ NEVER — hot path
const workspaceId = 'ws_inneranimalmedia';
.bind('au_871d920d1233cbd1', 'ws_inneranimalmedia');
if (user.email === 'sam@inneranimalmedia.com') …

// ✅ ALWAYS — resolve from session / token / authorization row
const userId = authUser.id;
const workspaceId = row.workspace_id ?? (await resolveRequestWorkspaceId(env, authUser, url));
const tenantId = authRow.tenant_id ?? workspaceRow.tenant_id;
```

## Allowed literals (not “identity”)

- **OAuth registry key:** `MCP_CANONICAL_CLIENT_ID` from `mcp-oauth-shared.js` only (maps to D1 `oauth_clients.client_id`) — do not duplicate the string elsewhere.
- **Scope names:** `iam:profile`, `mcp:tools`, `iam:agent` (protocol strings).
- **Table/column names:** `auth_users`, `agentsam_mcp_oauth_tool_allowlist`, etc.
- **Public URLs:** `https://mcp.inneranimalmedia.com`, issuer hostnames (not user-specific).

## Auth / MCP protocol must be D1-driven

| Concern | Source of truth | Runtime reads |
|---------|-----------------|---------------|
| OAuth client | `oauth_clients` | `mcpOAuthLoadClient(env, clientId)` |
| External app (ChatGPT/Claude) | `agentsam_mcp_oauth_external_client_registry` | `resolveExternalClientKeyFromRedirect` |
| User may connect ChatGPT/Claude | `agentsam_mcp_oauth_user_client_allowlist` | `assertUserMayUseExternalClient` — rows from **consent approve**, never migration-seeded `au_*` |
| OAuth tool surface | `agentsam_mcp_oauth_tool_allowlist` | `loadMcpOAuthExternalToolKeys` |
| User tool allowlist | `agentsam_mcp_allowlist` | `findMcpAllowlistMatch` / session scope |
| Workspace on token | `oauth_authorizations.workspace_id` | token issue + `mcp_workspace_tokens` |

No second copy of allowlists, client lists, or “Sam’s workspace” in JavaScript.

## Migrations

- **Platform registry only:** `INSERT` into `agentsam_mcp_oauth_external_client_registry` (`chatgpt`, `claude`, `cursor`) — no `user_id`.
- **Never** seed `agentsam_mcp_oauth_user_client_allowlist` with operator `au_*` in SQL. First grant happens at OAuth consent (`recordExternalClientAllowlistOnConsent`).
- One-off data repair: resolve `user_id` from `auth_users` by email in a documented script — not copied into committed migration `VALUES`.

## Validation (required before ship)

```bash
npm run guard:identity          # OAuth/auth tier — must pass (CI gate)
npm run guard:identity:all      # Full repo audit (legacy HTML may still fail)
```

OAuth tier scans: `src/api/oauth.js`, `src/api/mcp-oauth*`, `src/core/mcp-oauth*`, `settings.js` (MCP paths), `migrations/`, MCP `mcp-oauth*` + `index.js`. Bridge/health use `env.WORKSPACE_ID` / `env.TENANT_ID` (wrangler vars), not JS literals.

## Quality flag

`HARDCODED_IDENTITY` — any PR or deploy that introduces forbidden literals. Block merge until removed or moved to D1 + dynamic resolve.
